---
description: Agent must not run destructive git (push, force, reset --hard, clean, branch -D, checkout/restore .). Human terminal is not blocked.
alwaysApply: true
---

## GIT GUARDRAILS — AGENT ONLY
- This rule binds the **AI agent**, not the developer's terminal. The user may still run any git command locally.
- When a destructive operation is needed, **explain the exact command** and **ask the user to run it** (or approve an explicit exception for this session).

## NEVER RUN (agent)
- `git push` (any variant, including `--force`, `--force-with-lease`)
- `git reset --hard`
- `git clean -f` / `git clean -fd` / `git clean -fx` (any destructive clean)
- `git branch -D` / `git branch --delete --force`
- `git checkout .` / `git restore .` (discard all working tree changes in cwd)
- Broad wipes such as `git stash clear` without explicit user request and understanding

## SAFE ALTERNATIVES (agent may use when appropriate)
- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git branch -a`, `git show`
- `git add`, `git commit` on a **feature branch** (never direct commit to `main` — code-quality.mdc)
- `git checkout -b`, `git switch` (non-destructive)
- `git stash push` / `git stash pop` when scoped and reversible (avoid `stash clear`)

## IF BLOCKED
- State clearly: the command is blocked by user policy.
- Offer: exact command for the user to run, or a safer sequence (e.g. backup branch before reset).
